    public interface ReturnPremiumPlan
extends com.guidewire.bc.domain.invoice.gen.ReturnPremiumPlanStubI
    ReturnPremiumPlan A ReturnPremiumPlan specifies how to allocate credits through a set of ReturnPremiumHandlingSchemes each uniquely identified by a ReturnPremiumHandlingCondition that identifies whether a scheme applies to a collection of (credit) InvoiceItems.

      • getDefaultHandlingSchemePriority

        int getDefaultHandlingSchemePriority()
        Returns the Priority of the default handling scheme of the return premium plan.

        The default handling scheme is distinguished by having Other as its Condition. No other handling scheme can have a lower priority (larger number value) that that of the default.

        Returns:
        The priority of the default return premium handling scheme.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if no Other handling scheme exists.

      • increaseHandlingSchemePriority

        void increaseHandlingSchemePriority(@Nonnull
                                  ReturnPremiumHandlingScheme scheme)
        Increase the priority of the specified handling scheme (switches priority with the next highest).
        Parameters:

        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the handling scheme priority is already the highest or is the Other handling scheme.
